67db7a20-fdaf-4120-9eae-1d3409cdf4a9.2bc318a8-691e-44cf-99e8-058e512fbc26.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
67db7a20-fdaf-4120-9eae-1d3409cdf4a9.3244eb7e-7c49-4052-97b1-6b68b2a1d35b.description=
Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

Responses\:
success -  The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

Returns\:
The raw result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Returns\:
Field 1 - The first value. Here for compatibility
Field 2 - The second value. Here for compatibility
Field 3 - The operation. Here for compatibility
formatted_result - The formatted result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.
67db7a20-fdaf-4120-9eae-1d3409cdf4a9.37dcb6c6-976a-4e97-9548-c008a7b11429.description=
Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

Inputs\:
matchType - The type of match to perform.
toMatch - The string to check if matches another string.
matchTo - The string to match against.
ignoreCase - Boolean value for whether or not to ignore case during match.

Responses\:
success - The String matched.
failure - The string did not match, or something went wrong.

Operation to check for valid IP address formats.

inputList\:  comma seperated list of variables to check

Reponsses\:

67db7a20-fdaf-4120-9eae-1d3409cdf4a9.description=
Summary\:
Component flow for createALiasAndZoneByLists.  This flow determines which aliases exist in fabrics within datacenter.  
- If exists, then build fabric data for ntap or cust side, (for zonecreate operator).
 - If not exist, then append $alicreate list, the wwpn of alias that needs creating.

Inputs
- Ntap_or_cust\: this flow is called twice in createAliasAndZoneByLists, once for ntap once for cust side.
- foreachAliases\: either  $NTAPlifNameList or $custHostnameList, depending on $ntap_or_cust
- foreachWwpns\: either $NTAPlifWwpnList or $custWwpnList, depending on $ntap_or_cust
- searchBrocadesByAliasXML\: XML Output from searchBrocadesByALLAliases (will re-iterate through each alias to find if exist)
- alicreateList\: If not exist, append to alicreateList, the wwpn that needs alicreation.   

Output
- alicreateList\: appended WWPN for each ntap and cust call of this flow, which needs alicreation.
- Global variables created\: ${fabric}_ntap and ${fabric}_cust \= $aliasesAreadyExist
